Earth Day has to be Earth Every Day, 

some of the things I try to do to make a positive difference, every day, in every way, 

we try to reduce, reuse, and recycle in every aspect of our lives, 

100% solar, we generate more than we use, 

currently adding batteries, 

100% rainwater capture system, for irrigation, 

we drive electric vehicles, powered by solar, 

100% LED lighting, 

we recycle everything--- organics, plastics, packaging, food waste, composting, electronics, 

we do everything possible to eliminate single use plastic packaging/products, 

we plant trees, 

we have a very large plant and native drought-tolerant, plant garden/landscape, 

I ride my bike, a lot, 

we have a solar hot water heating system, 

we eat a healthy, organic, local, plant-based diet, 

we shop with our own reusable bags, 

we use the internet, not trees, 

we advocate for climate education, 

we pick up trash, 

we do online billing 

we are pesticide free, 

we turn off lights/electronics, when we don’t need them, 

we use sola tubes, 

we use energy efficient appliances, 

we write letters to politicians, 

we support suitability in every way, 

we give speeches, 

we vote, 

we live like we talk,

We try constantly to do more, 

To do better, 

To be better, 

Shine on, heal on,

Bill Walton thinks 1986 Boston Celtics title teammate Danny Ainge should be in the Hall of Fame
 
By Justin Quinn, USA Today, Published June 17th at 6:00 am EST
 
Should champion Boston Celtics guard and former Celtics team president Danny Ainge be in the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame? If you ask his teammate from the 1986 Celtics title team, Bill Walton (himself a Hall of Famer), the answer is an unequivocal yes.
 
“I got to know Danny over some of his life,” shared Walton in a recent interview with Bally Sports’ Brandon “Scoop B” Robinson. “He’s quite a bit younger than I am. And then I got to rebound for him on the Boston Celtics; (there) wasn’t a lot of rebounds to be had there.
 
“I also got to guard his man and … got to inbound the ball to him as well.”
 
“It was super fun to be with him on that Celtics squad,” related Walton, reminiscing about what is widely regarded as one of the greatest teams ever assembled.
 
“He was a critical component and I’m shocked and dismayed that Danny Ainge is not in the Basketball Hall of Fame.”
